			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here is a tactic you might try if you're level 4-7 or so.  Try it on yellows, see if it works.<BR>
First cast minor shielding on yourself, then siphon strength from a blue con or something weak, also cast grim aura, and summon yourself a pet.  Now wait til your mana refills, then find a target.  Get just within casting distance.  Cast clinging darkness, then poison bolt, then disease cloud.  Your pet will be holding him off.  Then cast fear until the mob starts running away.  Since you are buffed up, you and your pet can chase after him and whoop him good.  Make sure your fear spell in particular will not be resisted though or else....
				</font>
			</td>

